HEADWORD: Rescissory
<hw>Re*scis"so*ry</hw> <pr>(r?-s?z"?-r? ⟦or⟧ r?-s?s"-)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>rescissorius</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>rescisoire</ets>.]</ety> <def>Tending to rescind;
rescinding.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To pass a general act <qex>rescissory</qex> (as it was called),
annulling all the Parliaments that had been held since the year
1633.</q> <rj><qau>Bp. Burnet.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

